<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="oppose-vt">oppose <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'pəʊz/    美 /ə'poʊz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>反对；抵制：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All the members present opposed the plan bitterly.
所有与会的成员都坚决反对这个计划。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>oppose doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I would oppose changing the law.
我反对改变这项法律。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>opposed /ə'pəʊzd/ adj [不用于名词前]  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His parents are <strong>opposed to</strong> the marriage.
他的父母反对这桩婚事。</p></div>

<h3 id="as-opposed-to">as opposed to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>而；而非：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Two hundred people attended the meeting, as opposed to 300 the previous year.
200人出席了这次会议，而前一年是300人。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We employ you to work as opposed to (= rather than) just sitting.
我们雇你是让你干活的，而不是让你光坐着。</p></div>

<p>opposing /ə'pəʊzɪŋ/ adj [只用于名词前]  </p></div>